    lng: -1.5459,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "Whit Monday (25 May 2026): three Morris sides dance through Bampton from morning until evening — in pub car parks, on street corners, in private gardens. Each side has a Fool in a jester's costume who carries a stick with an inflated pig's bladder attached. The Fool's job is to whack any dancer making a mistake, not gently. A Cake Bearer carries a fruit cake impaled vertically on a decorated sword — anyone who donates money receives a piece, said to bring good luck (for women, specifically, fertility). This is one of England's oldest continuously performed Morris traditions, documented in written records since the 18th century and almost certainly older. It lapsed only in 1917 and 1918 — every other year since Tudor times it has happened. Free to watch. Combine with the Bampton Community Archive (Old Grammar School building, also the Downton Abbey Cottage Hospital exterior) for context.",
