    lng: -1.5459,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "Spring Bank Holiday Saturday (23 May 2026): the Bampton Shirt Race, organised by SPAJERS (Society for the Preservation of Ancient Junketing). Teams of two dress in nightshirts and race a vehicle of their own design through Bampton, stopping at every pub to down a mandatory measure of ale before continuing. The race was invented in 1953 to celebrate the Coronation and has run every year since — the 14 pub stops celebrate the 14 pubs Bampton once supported. In the early years, nightshirts were relatively easy to find; now fancy dress is standard. All proceeds go entirely to Bampton's pensioners: cash gifts at Christmas, an annual party and an outing. Come to watch, cheer, and have lunch in one of the pubs.",
