    description: "Bampton Manor House is a substantial 18th-century building where, at some unspecified earlier date, the resident ghost was so powerful that conventional exorcism failed. The clergy called in eventually found only one method that worked: confining the entity inside a large barrel of beer. The barrel was then kept in the manor cellar — not removed, not destroyed, just stored. The current whereabouts of the barrel are unknown. Walk around the manor exterior (private house), visit the church directly next door, and combine with the Bampton Heritage Centre in the Old Grammar School building (Old Grammar School = Downton Cottage Hospital exterior): the archive holds photographs, documents, and a working model of Bampton's railway station. The nearby Holwell Farm (15 mins walk) had its own White Lady ghost, who reappeared at a second well when the first was filled in.",
