    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "A 1-mile village walk from your own back door. The church of St Mary the Virgin has a triangular locker in the chancel containing a preserved heart (William Holcott, 1575) — buried separately from his body, a medieval practice for people who died away from home. Find the Norman north door: it opens directly from the manor grounds — the private lord's entrance, still visible. The Crusade chest near the font has a coin-slot hole in the lid (donations for the Third Crusade, c.1190). Buckland House (visible from the lane) was a recusant Catholic safe house from 1586: the Throckmorton family concealed priests at a time when doing so was a capital offence. The west pavilion was the secret Catholic chapel. Sir Robert Throckmorton added the battlemented parapet to the church tower specifically to match the style of his new Palladian house.",
