    lng: -1.506,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "Gainfield is a farm and hamlet within Buckland parish. Its name — recorded in Domesday — derives from 'Game Field': a field where summer sports or games were held in Saxon times, and crucially where the Hundred of Ganfield assembled to administer justice, raise militia levies, and settle disputes. A Saxon hundred court would have met here in the open air, probably at a particular tree, with representatives from all 12 settlements in the hundred attending. Walk east from Buckland along the public footpath (20 minutes). The site looks entirely like a working farm today — no earthworks, no marker, no information board. The entire significance is invisible. That invisibility is the point.",
