    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "St Denys's Church, Stanford in the Vale, holds a silver London flagon from 1752 inscribed: 'This Flagon is dedicated...by Joseph Cox Esqr. and Kathe Sophia his wife as an humble testimony of their unfeign'd thanks to Almighty God for the recovery of their three children Thomas Sophia and Charlotte from the smallpox by inoculation anno 1752.' This is 44 years before Jenner's vaccine. The Cox family had three children variolated simultaneously, all three survived, and rather than quiet private thanks they donated a permanent altar piece so the story would be recorded forever. The church itself is founded as a Saxon minster in AD 939. The south porch bears the combined arms of York and Warwick (1470s), which sparked a persistent tradition it was built for the wedding of Anne Neville to Richard III — unsubstantiated, but specific. Horse & Jockey pub does food. 4 miles from Buckland.",
