    description: "Amy Robsart, wife of Robert Dudley (Queen Elizabeth I's favourite), was found dead at the bottom of stairs at Cumnor Place on 8 September 1560 — broken neck, almost certainly murder. The house is long gone, but her tomb is in St Michael's Church, Cumnor (find the monument in the church). The ghost of Amy was so problematic that nine Oxford parsons were brought in to exorcise it. The exorcism required trapping her spirit in 'Madam Dudley's Pond' — the pond reportedly never froze after this, even in the hardest winters. The pond no longer exists. Walk the village, find the church (Saxon origins, 12th-century tower), look for the Cumnor Place site (foundations only, in private land — visible from the lane), and search for the Cumnor Physic Well nearby (Grade II listed, mineral spring, documented since 1667).",
