    description: "Uffington Castle is an Iron Age hillfort immediately above the White Horse, with ramparts enclosing 8 acres. The views from inside the ramparts at dusk are among the best in the region: the Vale of White Horse to the north, the Berkshire Downs to the south, Swindon to the west, and in clear conditions the Chilterns to the east. Arrive 45 minutes before sunset, walk the rampart circuit (20 minutes), watch the light change over the Vale. The White Horse (below) is most coherent in form from this elevation. The Ridgeway path east takes you toward Wayland's Smithy in the gathering dark — the grove of beeches at Wayland's is eerie by torchlight.",
