    description: "Walk from Faringdon market square across the fields to Great Coxwell Tithe Barn — 3 miles on footpaths through working arable land. The barn appears suddenly from behind a hedgerow, its stone roof rising above the field. Visit the barn (free, NT), then continue on the footpath to Coleshill village (1 mile) for Blake's Kitchen café. The complete circuit (Faringdon → barn → Coleshill → Faringdon) is 7 miles. This is the walk William Morris did from Kelmscott — he would hire a horse cart or walk to Great Coxwell specifically to visit the barn. The same fields, the same hedgerows, the same sudden reveal.",
