    description: "Wytham Woods is owned by Oxford University and has been the site of continuous ecological research since 1947 — the longest unbroken wildlife study in the world. The great tit and blue tit populations here have been monitored in every breeding season for 78 years; the data have contributed to over 1,000 scientific publications. The woods are open to walkers with a free permit (register at wildcru.ox.ac.uk or arrive at the gate on the Eynsham road and sign in). The permit allows access on a network of footpaths. Spring (April–May): nesting season, bluebells, dawn chorus. Summer: woodland butterflies. Autumn: spectacular fungal diversity. Winter: roosting finch flocks. 8 miles from Buckland.",
