    description: "April–May: the Windrush flood meadows at Witney are carpeted in meadow buttercups, cuckooflower, and (in the right areas) snake's-head fritillary. The 3-mile meadow loop from Witney town follows the Windrush through the NT meadow areas and Cogges Farm, passing under willows and across footbridges. This is a traditional hay meadow landscape of the kind that has almost entirely disappeared from lowland England — the wildflower assemblage here has not changed since before the war. Finish at Cogges Farm café or the Butter Cross in Witney market for ice cream. The Windrush meadow is quietly one of the best spring wildflower walks within 10 miles.",
