    name: "Curlew Call Bingo at Chimney Meadows",
    category: "adventures",
    lat: 51.7088,
    lng: -1.4905,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "Make bingo cards at home before you go, with bird names in a grid: curlew, lapwing, snipe, redshank, skylark, reed bunting, sedge warbler, cuckoo, hobby, kingfisher. Sit near the bird hides at Chimney Meadows from April to June. First to hear — not just see — all their birds wins. The curlew's call is a rising, haunting bubble; the lapwing's is a drawn-out 'pee-wit'; the cuckoo needs no introduction. Chimney Meadows records around 100 bird species per year, including regular barn owls and occasional hobbies.",
