    name: "Otter Footprint Hunt with Plaster of Paris",
    category: "adventures",
    lat: 51.7140,
    lng: -1.4520,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "Pack plaster of Paris, a small bowl, and a spoon. Walk the soft mud margins of the Duxford Old River inside Chimney Meadows looking for otter prints: five-toed, webbed, about 6cm across, with a distinctive large heel pad. When you find one, mix a small batch of plaster and pour it carefully into the print. Wait 15 minutes. Lift out a perfect cast of an otter's foot. Also look for otter spraints — droppings left on prominent stones or roots with a distinctive sweet, musky smell. Frame it as: 'We're going to find the otter's secret messages and steal their footprints.'",
    whyCurious: "Otters vanished from the Thames for decades due to pesticides. They returned in the 1990s and are now established. The Duxford Old River — the ancient meander inside Chimney Meadows — is confirmed otter territory. A cast of an actual otter print is a trophy that lasts forever.",
