    name: "Gargoyle Grimace Competition at Bampton Church",
    category: "adventures",
    lat: 51.7180,
    lng: -1.5380,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "St Mary the Virgin in Bampton has an array of 15th-century gargoyles and grotesques on its parapets. Give each child a sketchbook: (a) count all the gargoyles on one face of the building, (b) draw your favourite in as much detail as possible, (c) reproduce the gargoyle's expression with your own face and photograph it side-by-side. Who can pull the most accurate gargoyle face? Display the expression photos and sketches side by side. Bampton is also the 'Downton Abbey' filming village — the church appears in the show.",
