    description: "St Mary's Longworth has a churchyard with legible 17th and 18th-century headstones. Give each child a worksheet to find: the oldest legible date, the longest name (count the letters), the most elaborate epitaph, the grave with the most symbols (skull and crossbones, an hourglass, carved angels), the name that sounds most modern. The 8-year-old can read the inscriptions; the 6-year-old spots the symbols. Inside, the church has medieval brasses and nave arches decorated with carved heads — give points for finding the carved heads and making up a one-sentence biography for each.",
