    category: "adventures",
    lat: 51.7100,
    lng: -1.4930,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "Park on the lane between Buckland and Hinton Waldrist at dusk (30 minutes before sunset, October–February when owls hunt earlier). Face a rough grass field margin or hedgerow base. Assign each family member a different window or direction. The first person to spot something white drifting silently over the field margin wins. Barn owls quarter these rough edges hunting voles, flying low and slow with a buoyant flapping-gliding pattern. They are almost completely silent and almost completely white — they look exactly like a ghost. Frame it as: 'We're going ghost hunting.'",
