    lng: -1.5200,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "Along any ancient hedgerow between Buckland and Radcot, collect one leaf each from as many different tree and shrub species as you can find — hawthorn, blackthorn, field maple, elder, dog rose, hazel, spindle, crab apple. Back at a flat surface (the boot of the car, a picnic blanket), lay each leaf on white paper and draw around the silhouette in pencil. Who got the most genuinely different silhouettes? Then use a tree ID app or field guide to name each one. The classic 'Hooper's Rule' says each tree species per 30-metre stretch of hedge represents approximately 100 years of age — so count the species and estimate the hedge's age.",
