    category: "adventures",
    lat: 51.7090,
    lng: -1.4910,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "Before a winter walk to Chimney Meadows (January–March), check the Environment Agency real-time river gauge for Shifford Lock online. Note the current reading. Find a fixed reference point at Chimney Meadows — a fence post, a gate bolt — and measure where the water reaches. Was the forecast right? Return after rain and check again. Over multiple visits, build a simple chart of gauge reading vs water level at your marker. The 8-year-old manages the data; the 6-year-old does the measuring; this can run as a project all winter.",
