    name: "Cowslip Carpet Walk at Chimney Meadows (April–May)",
    category: "adventures",
    lat: 51.7090,
    lng: -1.4900,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "In late April to early May, Chimney Meadows turns yellow with cowslips. Walk to the southern sections of the reserve and stand in a carpet of nodding yellow flowers. Challenge: count all the cowslips in a 2-metre circle without moving. Then count a second circle — which has more? Are they near the ditch or further away? The 2-year-old will try to pick one (allow it — one flower per child is fine). The 6-year-old counts in one area while the 8-year-old counts in another. Compare results. Walk home with yellow-stained fingers.",
