    description: "Grey herons commute from their daytime fishing spots to their roost at dusk along fixed, predictable flightlines — they follow the river valley, flying in a direct line, slow and heavy, necks folded. Stand at Shifford Lock for 20 minutes just before dusk and count how many herons fly over. Each person has a counter or makes tally marks. Compare different evenings: do more herons fly over after a warm day? In winter or summer? After flood or drought? The 6-year-old holds the tally counter; the 8-year-old spots and calls.",
