    lng: -1.4340,
    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "St George's Church in Hatford (a tiny hamlet 3 miles east of Buckland) is an extraordinarily intact Norman church with a Saxon window still visible and a carved sundial in the stone above the south doorway. The church is usually open. Challenge: find the Saxon window (it's a distinctive round-headed double-light in the north wall, look for the change in stonework), find the sundial above the south door (it's carved directly into the lintel), and estimate what time the shadow would have fallen at midday. The church is small enough that a 6-year-old can find everything in 20 minutes. Completely off the tourist map.",
