    description: "Faringdon Folly's woodland (always open, always free) contains a growing collection of sculptures and hidden objects: 22 blackbird figures hidden throughout the trees, a giraffe, a storytelling chair, a 'useless bridge' that leads nowhere, a Mavka sculpture, and — somewhere in the woods — an old piano that someone installed and left. The challenge: find as many blackbirds as possible in 30 minutes. The trail is never the same twice because new objects appear. Bring a camera and photograph each find. The 8-year-old leads the hunt; the 6-year-old counts; the 2-year-old spots anything shiny.",
