    description: "On the muddy field edge of the footpath south of Buckland toward the Thames, look carefully for animal tracks in the soft ground after rain: rabbit (paired oval prints, toes forward), fox (diamond shape, single file), badger (five toes, wide flat), heron (large three-toed), mole hills (fresh loose soil). The 8-year-old photographs each track; the 6-year-old draws it in a notebook. At home, print the photographs and build a 'who crossed this field last night' detective wall. Return to the same spot after a dry spell and after wet — do different animals use the path in different weather?",
