    description: "When the Thames floodplain is flooded in January–February, park at the Trout Inn (Tadpole Bridge) and walk or drive slowly along the road embankment. Scan the flooded fields with binoculars. The species to count: teal (small, fast, green and brown), wigeon (chestnut-headed ducks, whistle like a toy), lapwing (black and white, tumbling flight), golden plover (golden-brown in winter flocks), grey heron (standing statue). Each child has a species to watch for and tallies sightings on a notebook. Hundreds of wildfowl concentrate on the flooded Vale in cold winters.",
