    type: "Adventure Idea",
    description: "The Cuckoopen Plantation at Coleshill (National Trust Green Walk) is a traditional isolated woodland copse on the estate boundary — 'cuckoo pens' are found across Britain wherever people once believed you could trap a cuckoo inside a circle of trees to keep summer from ending. Walk the Green Walk from Coleshill village to find it. Tell the children the story before you arrive: 'People used to believe if you caught the cuckoo you could stop summer leaving. They built this ring of trees to try.' The cuckoo always got away. Listen for the real cuckoo in May — this is still prime cuckoo territory.",
