    description: "The Emperor Dragonfly is Britain's largest dragonfly — brilliant turquoise-blue (male), long, fast, and territorial. In June–August, a male Emperor will patrol a fixed territory over a pond or the wider river, repeatedly flying the same oval circuit every 2–3 minutes. Find one at the Chimney Meadows pond hide, note his patrol route, and time his circuit. Who can predict exactly where he'll turn next? What happens when a second male enters his territory? (They will fight in the air — you may see a brief midair collision.) The 8-year-old times the circuits; the 6-year-old watches the territory boundary.",
