    description: "Stand close to (but not inside) the tower of Bampton's church and clap your hands sharply once. Time how long the echo takes to die away. The large stone tower creates a long reverb. Now try: a single sharp shout, a low note, a high note. Which sound reverberates longest? Does the east face sound different from the north? Compare results at a different, smaller church (Longworth or Hatford) and time those too. Which tower has the longest echo? The 8-year-old can use a phone timer; the 6-year-old does the clapping; the 2-year-old shouts.",
