    description: "Before arriving at Tadpole Bridge, each child makes their own boat at home from natural materials: a walnut shell hull, a twig mast, a leaf sail held with a blob of beeswax, a pebble ballast. Boats must use only natural materials (except a short piece of thread for the rigging if needed). Launch from the upstream rail of Tadpole Bridge and walk downstream along the Thames Path to see whose boat travels furthest before sinking or snagging. Judge on: distance travelled, how long it stays afloat, and whether the sail is still up at the end.",
