    description: "The Faringdon Folly Tower (built 1935 by the eccentric Lord Berners, the last major folly built in England) opens on selected Sundays April–October. The tower is 100ft high with 154 steps to the top. From the top, you can see the Thames, the Cotswolds, the Chilterns, and the Berkshire Downs — a 25-mile view. The surrounding woodland (always free and open) has the sculpture trail, hidden blackbird sculptures, and a deliberately useless bridge. Adults £3, ages 11–16 £1, under 11s free. The tower was closed for repairs in 2025–26 and was expected to reopen in summer 2026 — check faringdonfolly.org.uk before visiting.",
