    description: "In late April and early May, Badbury Clump (National Trust, SN7 7NL, free for NT members, £4 parking) becomes one of the most spectacular bluebell woods in Oxfordshire — nine acres of ancient beech woodland carpeted in blue, inside an Iron Age hillfort from around 600 BC. The Pink Walk (1.2 miles, woodland loop) is ideal for children: short, flat on the woodland floor, and threading through the bluebell carpet. Tell the children: this fort was here 2,600 years before we arrived. The trees they're walking under are growing in the ramparts. Challenge: find the outer ditch of the hillfort.",
