    description: "Oxfordshire ranks third in England for crop circles, and the Uffington area — White Horse Hill and the surrounding wheat fields — has historically been the most active local spot. The most recent confirmed formation was at Uffington Castle on 9 August 2020. Monitor temporarytemples.co.uk from late June each summer. If a formation is reported near Uffington, drive to the area and look for it from the Ridgeway or any public footpath with field views. Do NOT enter standing crops — view from footpaths only. The circle can sometimes be seen from the White Horse Hill viewpoint.",
