    description: "The Eagle and Child on St Giles' Street (known as the 'Bird and Baby') hosted the Inklings — C.S. Lewis, J.R.R. Tolkien, Charles Williams — in the back room called the Rabbit Room every Tuesday morning from the 1930s to 1962. Tolkien read early chapters of The Lord of the Rings aloud here before it was published. The pub is still a pub.",
    whyCurious: "The Rabbit Room at the back is the specific spot. A plaque marks it. Lewis and Tolkien met here so regularly that Lewis once described the ritual as more reliable than lectures. The pub moved the Inklings' meetings to the Lamb and Flag across the road in the 1960s — some scholars count both as Inklings venues.",
