    name: "Edmund Halley's House on New College Lane",
    lat: 51.7540,
    lng: -1.2530,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "historic-building",
    description: "At 7 New College Lane stands the house where Edmond Halley, who predicted the return of the comet that bears his name, lived and worked as Savilian Professor of Geometry from 1703 to 1742. A small plaque on the wall is the only marker. Tourists walking under the Hertford Bridge overhead rarely look right.",
    whyCurious: "Halley built a small observatory on the roof of this house — one of the earliest private observatories in Oxford. He used it to track lunar positions for the navigation tables that would eventually help calculate longitude at sea. The roofline is unchanged.",
