    type: "market",
    description: "Oxford's Covered Market, entered from the High Street or Market Street, has traded continuously since 1774. It contains butchers, fishmongers, bakers, cobblers, a barber, a hat shop, a flower stall, and several cafes — all inside a Victorian iron-and-glass roof. The market is free to enter and open Monday to Saturday.",
    whyCurious: "Ben's Cookies in the market has been making oversized warm cookies here since 1983 and remains the original shop. The butchers still sell game in season including pheasant and venison. The oldest shop — a tailor — has been in the same unit since the 1800s. Almost every Oxford local shops here; very few tourists find it.",
