    name: "Jericho — Oxford's Bohemian Canal Quarter",
    lat: 51.7605,
    lng: -1.2659,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "neighbourhood",
    description: "Jericho is a Victorian working-class neighbourhood west of central Oxford, built in the 1820s for workers at the Oxford University Press and the adjacent canal wharves. It now contains the Little Clarendon Street restaurant strip, the Phoenix Cinema, the Oxford Canal towpath, and some of the finest mid-Victorian terraced housing in the country.",
    whyCurious: "The Oxford Canal enters Oxford here and the towpath from Jericho northward to Wolvercote is one of the best urban walks in England — narrow boats moored every few hundred metres, locks, reed beds, herons. Jericho is also the setting for parts of Philip Pullman's His Dark Materials trilogy, including Jordan College (modelled on Exeter).",
