    description: "The Turf Tavern is reached through two narrow alleyways — either from Holywell Street through Bath Place or from New College Lane through a passage beside the city wall. It sits below ground level against the medieval city wall, parts of which form the pub's outer wall. It has traded continuously since the 13th century.",
    whyCurious: "Bob Hawke (future Prime Minister of Australia) drank his record yard-of-ale here as a Rhodes Scholar, a fact that is reportedly on his Wikipedia page and definitely on the pub's chalkboard. Bill Clinton famously 'did not inhale' here during his Oxford years. The garden in summer is one of the best sun-traps in the city.",
