    lng: -1.2494,
    category: "adventures",
    type: "boathouse",
    description: "Cherwell Boathouse at the end of Bardwell Road in North Oxford has been renting punts since 1904. The stretch of river here — the Cherwell above the Victoria Arms — is narrower and quieter than the Cherwell at Magdalen Bridge, with overhanging willows, moorhen families, and almost no other punters. The boathouse has a riverside restaurant open for lunch and dinner.",
    whyCurious: "This is where Oxford university students actually punt — not the tourist-heavy stretch by Magdalen. The river here has a mild current and no powered craft, making it suitable even for total beginners. In summer the bank beyond the boathouse is one of the finest picnic spots in Oxford and used almost exclusively by local families.",
