    description: "The Radcliffe Observatory in Green College (now part of the Radcliffe Department of Medicine) is an octagonal tower completed in 1794, modelled on the Tower of the Winds in Athens. It recorded daily meteorological observations from 1815 to 2004 — the longest continuous climate record in Britain. The building is now within a private medical college.",
    whyCurious: "The temperature and rainfall data from this tower, recorded by hand twice daily for 190 years, is one of the key datasets for British climate science. The tower exterior can be seen from Woodstock Road and is one of the most architecturally eccentric buildings in Oxford — a Greek classical monument in a suburb.",
