    description: "Christ Church Meadow Walk is a 2km loop around the southern meadow between the Cherwell and the Thames, freely accessible from the War Memorial Garden or from Rose Lane. The Cherwell side of the loop has a backwater called the New Cut where punts almost never go — the bank is reed-fringed and alive with warblers in spring.",
    whyCurious: "The meadow contains a herd of Longhorn cattle that graze it year-round to maintain its unimproved character. The cattle have right of way — walkers must step aside. On winter mornings, mist sits in the meadow at knee height and the cattle emerge from it like apparitions. Constable and Turner both painted views from approximately this spot.",
