    description: "Blackfriars Priory on St Giles' Street is a living Dominican community — friars in white habits live, pray and study here — with a chapel open to the public for morning Mass and evening prayer. It is also a Permanent Private Hall of Oxford University, meaning its students receive Oxford degrees. The building dates from 1921.",
    whyCurious: "It is one of only a handful of enclosed religious communities inside an English city centre. You can attend sung Compline on Sunday evenings — Gregorian chant in a working priory chapel 200 metres from a busy pub street. The friars also run a school of theology open to the public for evening lectures.",
