    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "church",
    description: "Keble College Chapel contains the original oil painting 'The Light of the World' by Holman Hunt (1851-53), one of the best-known Pre-Raphaelite works. Most people know the print; the original, 2 metres tall, is in a side chapel accessible free of charge during visiting hours. It is the painting that launched a thousand reproductions and is almost never crowded.",
    whyCurious: "The painting has a hidden symbolism Hunt later documented: the door Christ knocks on has no handle on the outside — it can only be opened from within, representing the soul's free will in responding to grace. The detail is too small to see in reproductions but visible in the original with the naked eye. The chapel itself is the largest in Oxford.",
