    description: "The Ashmolean Museum's Egypt gallery contains several unwrapped mummies, including one where the original hair is perfectly preserved — dark and still braided, more than 2,000 years old. The Ashmolean's Egyptian collection is the oldest in any museum in Britain, having received its first objects in 1683.",
    whyCurious: "The Ashmolean holds the Alfred Jewel — a 9th-century Anglo-Saxon object of gold, rock crystal and enamel, inscribed 'Aelfred mec heht gewyrcan' ('Alfred ordered me made') — almost certainly belonging to Alfred the Great. It is in a glass case you can stand 30cm from. The mummies and the Alfred Jewel together make this one of the most remarkable museum experiences in England.",
