    whyCurious: "The pub is technically accessible by road but the walk from the nearest bus stop is 20 minutes through fields. Most visitors arrive by punt or by the riverside footpath. On summer evenings, punts are stacked three deep at the mooring and the garden fills with people who feel they have discovered a secret. Technically it is in a village but feels like the countryside.",
