    whyCurious: "The square is used by tourists as a bus stop and ignored as a market. The same farmers have been bringing produce here for 20+ years. The cheese stall sells unpasteurised Oxford Blue from a farm in Burford at prices well below London farmers' market rates. Thursday's antique market has produced genuine finds including Oxford-printed 18th-century almanacs.",
