    lng: -1.2598,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "pub",
    description: "The Lamb and Flag on St Giles' Street, directly opposite the Eagle and Child, was the Inklings' Monday evening pub from the late 1940s onward, after the Bird and Baby became too crowded for their Tuesday meetings. The pub is owned by St John's College and profits go to fund student hardship. It is smaller, quieter and less touristy than its famous neighbour.",
    whyCurious: "The pub is almost never mentioned on Tolkien or Lewis walking tours, which all stop at the Eagle and Child opposite. Yet Lewis and Tolkien drank here more often in the decade before Lewis's death in 1963. A plaque inside is recent and easy to miss. The back room was their preferred spot.",
