    name: "The Latin Quarter — Oxford's Quiet Southern Colleges",
    lat: 51.7506,
    lng: -1.2530,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "neighbourhood",
    description: "The southern cluster of colleges — Oriel, Corpus Christi, Merton, Pembroke — is sometimes called the Latin Quarter (though not officially). It is quieter and less visited than the Broad Street area, with narrower medieval lanes, smaller quads, and fewer tourists. Corpus Christi has the smallest quad in Oxford and a tortoise called Jeremy who lives there.",
    whyCurious: "Corpus Christi's famous Pelican Sundial (1581) in the main quad is topped by a pelican, but close inspection shows it also has a perpetual calendar with movable parts. The tortoise (or its predecessor) has lived in the quad since the 1950s. The college's library contains one of the finest collections of Greek manuscripts in Britain.",
