    type: "pub",
    description: "The Trout Inn at Lower Wolvercote sits on an island in the Thames weir pool beside a cascade, with peacocks roaming the garden and a terrace above the rushing water. Lewis Carroll brought Alice Liddell here on river excursions. It is also featured in the Inspector Morse TV series and the His Dark Materials novels.",
    whyCurious: "The date on which Lewis Carroll first told the story of Alice — 4 July 1862 — is commemorated at the pub. The original rowing trip was from Folly Bridge downstream, but Carroll's diary records multiple visits to Godstow with the Liddell children, which would have passed here. The weir pool is the best spot in Oxford to watch a kingfisher in winter.",
