    type: "garden",
    description: "Oxford Botanic Garden, the oldest botanic garden in Britain (founded 1621), contains a Black Pine planted in 1645 — making it the oldest tree in Oxford and one of the oldest planted trees in Britain. It stands near the walled garden and has a plaque. The garden as a whole is tiny by standards of major botanic gardens and is correspondingly intimate.",
    whyCurious: "The Botanic Garden is where Philip Pullman set the final meeting of Lyra and Will in His Dark Materials — on a specific bench in the garden, 'the bench on the north side, under the rose wall.' The bench now has a small marker. The garden also holds the collection of plants used in the research that led to penicillin's discovery.",
