    type: "bookshop",
    description: "Thornton's Bookshop on Broad Street has been trading in second-hand and antiquarian books since 1835, making it the longest-established bookshop in Oxford. The interior is a narrow Victorian shopfront packed floor to ceiling with second-hand academic texts, paperbacks, and occasional rarities. The staff know the stock by heart.",
    whyCurious: "The shop is a few doors from Blackwell's but is immediately distinguishable — it smells of old paper and has no corporate signage. First editions and signed copies turn up in the general stock regularly, priced by condition rather than collectibility. The basement is occasionally opened for overflow and contains genuine finds.",
