    category: "strange-or-historic",
    type: "public-art",
    description: "Brasenose College takes its name from a 'brazen nose' — a bronze doorknocker in the shape of a nose that hung on the original college gate. The original knocker was removed to Stamford in 1330 when a group of scholars fled there during a university dispute. Brasenose College eventually bought back the building in Stamford (in 1890) specifically to recover the knocker. It now hangs in the college hall.",
    whyCurious: "The college was founded in 1509, named after a doorknocker it didn't own. The Stamford building was purchased 380 years later for a very large sum — effectively the most expensive doorknocker repurchase in history. A replica hangs on the current gate. The original, darkened with age, is on the wall of the hall.",
