    lng: -1.2539,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "library",
    description: "Below the Radcliffe Camera's famous circular drum is an underground reading room that connects to the Old Bodleian via a tunnel. The underground space — the Radcliffe Camera Lower Camera — is used as a Bodleian reading room and is accessible only to registered readers. The tunnel was built in the 1970s and carries a book conveyor belt.",
    whyCurious: "The underground tunnel between the Camera and the Bodleian is one of Oxford's genuine hidden spaces. Books are requested electronically and travel by automated conveyor through the tunnel. Registered readers can walk through it themselves — the experience of being underground between two of the most famous library buildings in the world is not described in any guidebook.",
