    lat: 51.7551,
    lng: -1.2491,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "church",
    description: "St Cross Church at the end of Holywell Street is a Norman and Early English church largely hidden from view behind college walls. The churchyard, shaded by large yews, contains the graves of Kenneth Grahame (author of The Wind in the Willows) and the painter William Egley. The lane leading to it — Dead Man's Walk — runs along the base of the old city wall.",
    whyCurious: "Dead Man's Walk is a walled alley running from Merton Street to the Botanic Garden, historically the route along which Jewish dead were carried for burial outside the city walls when the Jewish cemetery existed at the south end. It is one of the most atmospherically bleak lanes in Oxford and completely unmarked on tourist maps.",
