    name: "North Parade Avenue Market — Saturday Local Market",
    lat: 51.7649,
    lng: -1.2594,
    category: "food-or-treats",
    type: "market",
    description: "North Parade Avenue in north Oxford hosts a Saturday morning street market from 8am to 1pm — one of the best-supplied local producers' markets in Oxfordshire. Cheese, bread, seasonal veg, jams, plants, and fish arrive from farms and producers within 30 miles. The street itself is a Victorian shopping parade of independent businesses.",
    whyCurious: "North Oxford is a wealthy Victorian suburb built from 1860 onward for married dons (Oxford academics only gained the right to marry in 1877, and they immediately required houses). The streets were laid out to a generous plan with broad avenues and are lined with North Oxford Gothic villas. The market is run by and for residents rather than tourists.",
