    name: "Encaenia — Oxford's Annual Degree Ceremony in Latin",
    lat: 51.7542,
    lng: -1.2542,
    category: "events",
    type: "ceremony",
    description: "Encaenia is Oxford's annual honorary degree ceremony, held in the Sheldonian Theatre in June. Honorary degrees are conferred on distinguished figures in a ceremony conducted partly in Latin; the Public Orator delivers a speech on each recipient. Guests in academic dress process through the city from All Souls College to the Sheldonian with marshals carrying maces.",
    whyCurious: "The procession passes through central Oxford at noon on a Wednesday in June with no barriers and no advance notice in tourist guides. You can stand on Broad Street and watch Nobel laureates, prime ministers, and cultural figures walking past in medieval dress. Past recipients include Nelson Mandela, Seamus Heaney, and Bill Clinton.",
