    description: "The Jericho Tavern on Walton Street in Jericho is a pub music venue where Radiohead (then called On a Friday) played some of their earliest gigs in the late 1980s and early 1990s. The venue has operated since the 1970s as an independent music pub and continues to book touring and local acts on a small stage in the back room.",
    whyCurious: "Before Radiohead were Radiohead, they played the back room of a Jericho pub to 20–30 people. The room is essentially unchanged. The venue is still functioning and books live music most weekends. Tickets cost less than £10. The pub itself serves a good pint and is frequented almost entirely by locals.",
