    description: "The East Oxford Farmers' and Community Market takes place on Saturdays from 10am on Rymers Lane near Cowley Road. It focuses on local growers, artisan food producers, and community stalls — organic vegetables, sourdough, honey, seedlings, homemade preserves. The market has operated continuously since 2003 and is community-owned.",
    whyCurious: "The market is specifically designed to serve the ethnically diverse east Oxford community and deliberately stocks ingredients for South Asian, Middle Eastern, and African cooking alongside standard British produce. You can buy organic chillies, fresh fenugreek, Oxfordshire honey, and sourdough rye from the same market.",
