    category: "food-or-treats",
    type: "ice-cream-cafe",
    description: "G&D's (George and Danvers) is an Oxford institution with several branches, including one on St Aldate's open until 1am (or 2am at weekends). It serves homemade ice cream, cakes, and panini to students returning from late-night libraries and clubs. The flavours include seasonal specials and the Oxford Blue (with real Oxford Blue cheese).",
    whyCurious: "Finding excellent ice cream at midnight is unusual. G&D's has served Oxford late-night for over 25 years and is as much a rite of passage as a dessert option. The Oxford Blue flavour is sharp, sweet, and peculiar — exactly as it sounds. The queues on summer evenings extend onto the pavement and include academics, students, and tourists in roughly equal measure.",
