    whyCurious: "In an era of chain hairdressers and blow-dry bars, a barber operating in a Victorian market hall with original fittings is genuinely unusual. The prices have risen but are still well below modern salon equivalents. Several Oxford professors have been having their hair cut here by the same family for 40 years.",
