    description: "St Antony's College on Woodstock Road is Oxford's graduate college for international studies, founded 1953 with a bequest from a French merchant of disputed background. Its alumni include an unusually high proportion of senior intelligence officials, diplomats, and heads of state from multiple countries. The college's Middle East Centre library is the largest specialist collection in Britain.",
    whyCurious: "The college was founded with money from a French merchant named Antonin Besse, about whose wartime activities rumours have circulated for decades. Former CIA and MI6 officers have been fellows; multiple foreign heads of state and prime ministers studied here. Its common rooms are described by alumni as unlike any other Oxford college — multilingual, stateless, and permanent with intrigue.",
