    name: "The Oxford Punt — How to Self-Hire Without Getting Soaked",
    lat: 51.7522,
    lng: -1.2473,
    category: "adventures",
    type: "activity",
    description: "Self-hire punts are available from Magdalen Bridge Boathouse at the east end of the High Street. The upstream direction — heading north on the Cherwell toward the University Parks and Marston — is quieter and shallower than the downstream (Christchurch Meadow) route. Most tourist guides send visitors downstream; the upstream backwaters are calmer, the banks narrower, and the kingfisher sightings more reliable.",
    whyCurious: "The upstream Cherwell above the Rollers passes through the University Parks and under a series of small wooden footbridges almost too low to punt beneath. The channel becomes very narrow north of Mesopotamia island — a strip of land between two branches of the river accessible only on foot — where overhanging willows almost close the waterway entirely. Locals go upstream; tourists go down.",
