    name: "Uffington Castle Hillfort Interior",
    lat: 51.5757,
    lng: -1.5699,
    category: "strange-or-historic",
    type: "Iron Age hillfort",
    description: "The hillfort above the White Horse has ramparts still six metres high in places, enclosing about eight acres. Inside, the ground is curiously level — a flat plateau that in summer fills with skylarks and in winter fills with cloud. The entrance on the northwest is original, a classic Iron Age inturned entrance forcing attackers into a killing ground between the rampart ends. Almost no excavation has been done inside. What is here is mostly unknown.",
