    lng: -1.4253,
    category: "strange-or-historic",
    type: "WW2 remains",
    description: "RAF Grove was built in 1942 as a satellite airfield for the Maintenance Command. The runways were demolished and the site became the Grove Business Park and housing estate, but the dispersal tracks, perimeter roads, and some blast pen outlines survive in the field pattern and road alignments around the modern estate. Walking the footpaths around the eastern edge of Grove, you cross concrete taxi-ways that once led USAAF and RAF aircraft to their dispersal points. Some sections are still in use as farm tracks.",
    whyCurious: "The ghost of the airfield is completely legible in the landscape if you know what to look for. The dead straight roads that go nowhere, the right-angle bends, the concrete aprons now serving as barn floors — WW2 is still here, just re-used.",
