    description: "In the field immediately behind the village church at Letcombe Regis, a dry moat of considerable size still marks the boundary of a medieval manor house long since demolished. The moat is now a raised ridge of earth around a rectangular depression — a classic moated manor site. The church dates from the 12th century and the moated manor was almost certainly contemporary with it. No interpretation boards, no signs, no visitors. The cows ignore it.",
