    type: "village green",
    description: "Fernham is a hamlet that sits slightly off the road between Faringdon and Wantage, possessing a triangular village green with an ancient oak, stone cottages, and a complete absence of modern intrusion. It appears in guidebooks rarely and in tourist literature almost never. The pub — the Woodman — is a genuine local pub with no ambitions. The green floods slightly in wet winters, leaving a rim of dried mud around the grass when it recedes. There is not a great deal to do here. That is entirely the point.",
