    name: "Kingston Lisle's Locked Estate Road",
    lat: 51.5978,
    lng: -1.5338,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "estate village",
    description: "Kingston Lisle village exists in the shadow of Kingston Lisle Park, a Georgian house set in a landscaped park that sweeps down from the Ridgeway. The estate road runs from the Blowing Stone's roadside position up through the park and is gated. The estate cottages in the village have a uniformity that marks them as purpose-built — the same stone, the same proportions, the same date. Walking through, the contrast between the controlled estate character and the wild Downs visible above is stark.",
