    name: "Wantage Vale and Downland Museum",
    lat: 51.5878,
    lng: -1.4267,
    category: "rainy-day",
    type: "local museum",
    description: "An underrated local museum in a converted stable block behind Church Street, covering the archaeology, social history, and trades of the Vale. The collection includes significant Iron Age material from the Downs, a reconstructed Victorian chemist shop, and items relating to the Wantage Tramway including a replica section of track. The Alfred the Great collection is necessarily speculative — almost no physical objects survive from his reign — but the historical context provided is thoughtful and honest about what is not known.",
