    name: "Kite's Nest Farm, Broadway (near Bourton)",
    lat: 52.028,
    lng: -1.832,
    category: "nature",
    type: "regenerative farm",
    description: "Kite's Nest Farm near Bourton has been farmed without artificial inputs since the 1980s by the Wright family, predating the current regenerative agriculture movement by decades. The farm runs native breed cattle and manages its hedgerows and grasslands on long rotations. The result is a farm that looks dramatically different from its conventional neighbours — taller hedges, rougher grass margins, a visibly higher density of insects and birds. The farm has been studied by Oxford University ecologists.",
