    description: "The Anchor Inn has marks inside showing flood levels from various years. The Vale floods regularly and Stanford in the Vale has been caught by high water on the Ock numerous times. The 2007 floods were exceptionally severe across the Vale and the mark from that year is significantly above the others. The inn's name is either coincidentally or deliberately appropriate — it has sat through many floods and remained anchored.",
