    description: "From certain positions on the Downs above Wantage, the midsummer sunset aligns with specific valley features in a way that is either remarkable coincidence or deliberate Neolithic landscape planning. The alignment has been noted by local archaeologists but not formally published. Whether prehistoric people arranged monuments to frame sunsets or whether human pattern-recognition is constructing the alignment retrospectively is genuinely unresolved. What is certain is that the view from the Downs at midsummer sunset is spectacular regardless of interpretation.",
