    name: "Buscot Park's Water Garden",
    lat: 51.6697,
    lng: -1.6531,
    category: "nature",
    type: "formal garden",
    description: "Harold Peto's water garden at Buscot Park creates a formal Italian axis from the house to the lake, using a canal, bridges, clipped yew, and a sequence of water features. It is one of the most complete Edwardian formal garden designs in England and sits within the National Trust's Buscot estate. The alignment of the water garden frames the distant views across the Thames meadows. The Faringdon Collection inside the house includes Rembrandt, Burne-Jones (a complete series of Briar Rose panels), and Reynolds.",
