    name: "The Lambourn Down's Racehorse Schooling Fences",
    lat: 51.5189,
    lng: -1.5412,
    category: "strange-or-historic",
    type: "equestrian infrastructure",
    description: "Scattered across the Downs above Lambourn are sets of schooling fences — practice National Hunt obstacles used to teach young racehorses to jump. They look incongruous in the open downland: constructed brush fences, open ditches, upright hurdles arranged in lines that don't follow any public path. Some are maintained, some are dilapidated. Approaching them on foot, the scale becomes apparent — they are built for animals considerably larger and faster than a person.",
