    name: "The Oxfordshire Way at Bampton",
    lat: 51.7263,
    lng: -1.5389,
    category: "adventures",
    type: "long distance path",
    description: "The Oxfordshire Way long-distance footpath passes through Bampton on its route from Bourton-on-the-Water to Henley. The section around Bampton crosses the Thames flood plain — in winter this requires the path to be essentially impassable without rubber boots and a tolerance for ankle-deep water. In summer the same section passes through hay meadows with tall grass and ox-eye daisies. The path is not heavily used and the Thames flood plain character — flat, big skies, distant willows — is unlike most of Oxfordshire.",
