    name: "Charney Bassett's Tiny Perfect Church",
    lat: 51.6473,
    lng: -1.4507,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "Norman church",
    description: "St Peter's at Charney Bassett is a Norman church of the smallest possible scale — a nave, a chancel, and a south doorway with scallop-capital columns. The village is barely larger than the churchyard. Inside, the proportions are so intimate that the altar seems almost within reach from the back pew. There is a 14th century effigy of a cross-legged knight of considerable quality for such a small village — evidence that someone significant was buried here.",
