    category: "strange-or-historic",
    type: "lost church site",
    description: "East Challow once had its own medieval church that was demolished in the 19th century when the parish was amalgamated with West Challow. The site of the church is marked by a raised rectangular mound in a field adjacent to the village — the churchyard mound, elevated above surrounding land by centuries of burials, is a standard indicator of a lost church site. The mound has never been excavated. The memorial stones were removed or buried.",
