    name: "Wantage's Elizabethan Almshouses",
    lat: 51.5885,
    lng: -1.4257,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "historic almshouses",
    description: "The almshouses in Mill Street, Wantage, were founded in the Elizabethan period and the surviving range, though much repaired, preserves the original plan of a quadrangle with individual chambers for elderly poor. The endowment came from a local family whose name is now forgotten even in Wantage. The almshouses are still occupied as housing. The stone used is the local ferruginous limestone that gives Wantage buildings their characteristic brown-orange tone different from the cream limestone of the Cotswolds.",
