    name: "Odstone Hill's Isolated Sarsen",
    lat: 51.5534,
    lng: -1.5834,
    category: "nature",
    type: "glacial erratic / sarsen",
    description: "On the open Downs southwest of Uffington, a single large sarsen stone sits in a field with no obvious relationship to any path, monument, or boundary. It is not on any archaeological record but is clearly an in-situ stone that has not been moved. Sarsens of this size are becoming increasingly rare on the Downs as many were removed in the 18th and 19th centuries for building material. This one survived because it was too large or too inconveniently positioned to move. It is about 2 metres long and partially buried.",
