    name: "Great Faringdon Market — Monthly Livestock",
    lat: 51.6564,
    lng: -1.5868,
    category: "events",
    type: "agricultural market",
    description: "Faringdon's Thursday market retains some of its agricultural character and the town still has the infrastructure of a Vale market town — wide central area, pub proximity to the market square, the whole layout designed for the weekly assembly of farmers and buyers. The livestock element has diminished but the market retains genuine local traders rather than the homogenised artisan market products found elsewhere. On market day the square is busy with people who actually live there, buying things they actually need.",
