    description: "Hinton Waldrist has earthwork remains of a medieval fortified manor on a slight rise above the Thames flood plain. The moat, though partially infilled, is still legible as a surrounding ditch and the interior platform is elevated above the surrounding field. The 'Waldrist' element of the name refers to a Norman family who held the manor — the de la Warr family — and the manor was their principal residence. The current village is small and quiet, the medieval earthworks in the fields behind the church.",
