    lat: 51.6391,
    lng: -1.5058,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "vernacular architecture",
    description: "Stanford in the Vale has an unusually complete survival of 17th-18th century farmhouses in its central core — buildings that date from a period of agricultural prosperity when the Vale clay farms were large and productive enough to fund substantial stone houses. Several are listed, including a 17th century farmhouse with original mullioned windows and, in one case, a complete range of outbuildings contemporary with the house. The village expanded along the road on a pre-enclosure plan that is still legible.",
