    lat: 51.6564,
    lng: -1.5868,
    category: "hidden-places",
    type: "coaching inn remains",
    description: "The Bell Hotel in Faringdon's market square has a rear courtyard that preserves the layout of a 17th century coaching inn — the stable range, the coach house, the pump in the centre, the upper gallery of the inn building. This is the architecture of the coaching era: the functional machine for processing travellers and horses. The courtyard is now used for parking but the Georgian brick ranges are complete and the ironwork of the stable stalls is still in place in one range.",
