    name: "The Ridgeway's Ancient Finger Post at Blowingstone Hill",
    lat: 51.5978,
    lng: -1.5338,
    category: "strange-or-historic",
    type: "historic waymarker",
    description: "The junction of the lane from Kingston Lisle with the Ridgeway track above is marked by an old finger post — a cast-iron direction sign from the early 20th century, possibly replacing an earlier wooden post. These finger posts once directed travellers at every Ridgeway junction. Many have been removed, damaged, or replaced with modern waymarkers. This one, at the head of Blowingstone Hill lane, has survived and still points in the original directions with the original lettering, though weathered almost to illegibility.",
