    type: "birdwatching hide",
    description: "The Ashgrave Hide on the Otmoor RSPB reserve overlooks the scrape and wet grassland managed for waders. In summer, lapwings and redshanks breed here; in winter, golden plover and jack snipe use the wet margins. The hide is reached by a 1.5-mile walk from the Roman Road car park.",
