    whyCurious: "The contrast between the pre-1820 contour canal (which wanders extravagantly to avoid earthworks) and the post-1820 straight cuts is visible on the map and on the water. Canal historians regard the Oxford as England's most characterful canal precisely because the two engineering philosophies coexist.",
