    description: "Otmoor is sometimes described as a square mile of wetland, though it is somewhat larger. The specific management of the RSPB reserve within it has created a mosaic of habitats — reedbed, wet grassland, scrape, and seasonal flood — that holds over 200 bird species annually and is one of the top inland birdwatching sites in central England.",
    whyCurious: "The RSPB acquired this site specifically because it was agriculturally marginal and could be re-wetted. In under 30 years it has transformed from drained arable to one of England's most productive wildlife sites — a conservation success story playing out invisibly to most Oxfordshire residents.",
