    description: "Boarstall Tower is a 14th-century fortified gatehouse on the eastern edge of Otmoor, all that remains of a moated medieval manor house. The tower is now owned by the National Trust and is one of the best examples of a medieval gatehouse in the region. The duck decoy in the grounds is one of the few remaining working examples in England.",
