    category: "food-or-treats",
    type: "canal pub",
    description: "The pubs along the Oxford Canal at Kidlington and Thrupp were historically as much a part of the canal infrastructure as the locks — places where boatmen could eat, sleep, stable horses, and conduct business. The surviving canal pubs retain the layout and character of working boatmen's pubs rather than leisure marina bars.",
