    type: "Roman religion",
    description: "The Roman shrine at Woodeaton produced hundreds of votive objects — miniature axes, wheels, figurines of gods, coins with holes for suspension — that are now in the Ashmolean Museum in Oxford. The wheel symbol is associated with the Celtic sun god and with healing, suggesting the shrine had a therapeutic or protective function.",
