    category: "strange-or-historic",
    type: "equestrian history",
    description: "The agricultural land around Bicester has been hunted by the Bicester and Warden Hill Hunt (formerly the Garth Hunt) since the 18th century. The hedgerow pattern of the countryside east of Bicester was partly maintained specifically for fox hunting — wide hedges, large fields, few wire fences — and this hunting landscape is still visible.",
