    whyCurious: "The temperature differential between the river water and the cold reservoir outflow creates a micro-climate around Pinkhill that produces unusual morning mists. The lock island here supports a dense population of grass snakes attracted by the warm southern bank and the abundant frog and toad population in the nearby wet meadows.",
