    whyCurious: "Wolvercote Paper Mill produced paper for the Oxford University Press for over three centuries, drawing water from the Thames through this stretch. The Press's distinctive Oxford Bible paper was made here until the mill closed in 2004. The lock area is now a quiet gateway into Oxford that most city visitors never find.",
