    description: "The Trout at Godstow is one of Oxford's most celebrated pubs, sitting beside the weir stream and the ruins of Godstow Nunnery. Peacocks roam the terrace, and the weir creates a constant backdrop of rushing water. Lewis Carroll, Inspector Morse, and generations of Oxford students have drunk here.",
    whyCurious: "Inspector Morse filmed several scenes at the Trout, and the pub appears in Colin Dexter's novels. Lewis Carroll is said to have drunk here on the expedition that inspired Alice in Wonderland — though Folly Bridge is more directly connected. The peacocks have lived at the Trout for so long that no one is certain when they arrived.",
