    description: "Wytham Creek drains the low ground between the Thames and Wytham Hill before rejoining the river near King's Lock. The creek flows through the edge of Wytham Great Wood, owned by Oxford University and one of the most studied woodlands on earth, famous for tit and deer research spanning eight decades.",
    whyCurious: "Wytham Great Wood has been continuously studied by Oxford ecologists since 1947, making it arguably the world's best-documented woodland. The great tit population here underpins much of what we know about natural selection in wild animals. From the Thames bank you can see the wood rising behind the creek, utterly unremarkable-looking for somewhere so scientifically important.",
