    whyCurious: "Osney Abbey's bells were moved to Christ Church and became Oxford's famous 'Great Tom' and its companions. So the bells that have regulated Oxford life for centuries came from an abbey that is now a residential street and a nature reserve. The abbey's footprint is largely built over and almost entirely unknown to Oxford visitors.",
