    whyCurious: "Christ Church has resisted every attempt to run a road through the meadow since the Victorian era. The meadow was grazed by longhorn cattle as a medieval survival until recently and retains an extraordinary flora. From the river bank you look back at Oxford's dreaming spires framed by open meadow — the quintessential view that has defined the city's self-image.",
