    whyCurious: "The Sandford Lasher is one of the Thames's most dangerous features and is marked by a stone tablet recording fatalities including two King's Scholars from Christ Church. The pull of the weir is deceptive — the surface looks calm but the undertow is lethal. The death toll here runs into dozens over recorded history.",
