    description: "Dorchester Abbey is a large Augustinian abbey church on the edge of the village where the River Thame meets the Thames. Founded as an early Christian cathedral see in 634 AD, it contains the remarkable Jesse Window — a medieval stone tracery showing the genealogy of Christ through a carved stone tree growing from Jesse.",
    whyCurious: "The Jesse Window at Dorchester is unique: instead of painted glass alone, the stone tracery itself is carved into branches and figures, so the window is simultaneously architecture and sculpture. The whole composition grows from a recumbent figure of Jesse at the base. Nothing quite like it exists elsewhere in England.",
