    description: "Wallingford Bridge has medieval origins and crosses the Thames at the town's historic centre. Nearby are the substantial earthwork remains of Wallingford Castle, once one of the largest Norman fortresses in England and the last castle to hold out for the Royalists in the Civil War, surrendering in 1646.",
    whyCurious: "Wallingford Castle held out against Parliamentarian forces for sixty-five days after the war had effectively ended elsewhere in England — the garrison simply refused to believe the king had surrendered. The castle's earthworks, now a public park, enclose the largest earthwork bailey in England. Agatha Christie lived nearby and used Wallingford in her fiction.",
