    whyCurious: "The lock at Goring was the scene of a notable Victorian social event: George Sanger's circus elephants were marched across the weir footbridge in the 1890s during the annual circus migration between grounds. The elephants reportedly showed no concern about the rushing water below. The lock keeper allegedly had significant concerns on their behalf.",
