    category: "adventures",
    type: "ancient trackway",
    description: "The Ridgeway National Trail descends from the Berkshire Downs at Streatley to cross the Thames by the bridge at Goring. This is the point where Britain's oldest road, the Ridgeway, meets the river. The hill above Streatley offers panoramic views over the Goring Gap and the Thames valley.",
    whyCurious: "The Ridgeway is believed to be at least 5,000 years old — one of the most ancient long-distance routes in the country. Its descent to the Thames at Goring-Streatley was a major prehistoric crossing point, and the concentration of Bronze Age and Neolithic monuments in the surrounding hills reflects the route's ancient significance.",
