    whyCurious: "The River Pang is one of England's finest chalk streams, rising near East Ilsley and flowing entirely through chalk geology. Its water is clearer than glass and maintains a constant cool temperature, making the confluence with the Thames a meeting of two very different river personalities. Kenneth Grahame lived at Pangbourne and the area inspired Wind in the Willows.",
