    whyCurious: "Grahame wrote Wind in the Willows partly out of his own desire to escape the pressures of his professional life into a timeless riverside world. The Pangbourne stretch of the Thames, with its backwaters, willows, and sense of hidden animal life, corresponds very closely to the landscape of the book. Mole, Rat, Toad, and Otter lived somewhere near here.",
