    whyCurious: "This eight-mile section of the Thames Path traverses flood-plain that has barely changed since the medieval period. The route passes Iffley, Sandford, and multiple unnamed backwaters that appear on old river maps but are invisible from roads. Heron, kingfisher, and otter are all regularly seen on this section.",
