    whyCurious: "The Sutton Pools were created by the construction of Culham Cut in 1809, which left the old river channel to develop into a network of quiet water. The backwaters flood regularly and drain slowly, creating a mosaic of water depth and vegetation that is one of the richest freshwater habitats on the Thames.",
