    whyCurious: "Red Triassic sandstone is not expected in the chalk and clay Thames valley, and the cliffs at Long Wittenham and Clifton Hampden represent erosion remnants of a much more widespread older geology. The stone was quarried for local buildings and gives both villages their distinctive warm colour that contrasts with the grey Cotswold stone to the west.",
