    whyCurious: "The collision of Victorian engineering with the pastoral Thames landscape has a particular drama at Appleford — a 125 mph express train thundering across a river that is otherwise experienced at walking pace. The bridge's lattice ironwork creates an elegant shadow pattern on the water below in low morning light.",
