    whyCurious: "Wolvercote Common, Port Meadow, and the surrounding water meadows form the largest area of unimproved common land in any English city. The combination of grazing animals, medieval management, and regular flooding has preserved plant communities that have been continuous since at least the Domesday period. Fungi here include species found nowhere else in Oxfordshire.",
