    whyCurious: "Mapledurham Mill has ground flour continuously since at least the Domesday period, though the current machinery is Victorian. It is the sole survivor of the dozens of mills that once used the Thames's water power. Alexander Pope visited Mapledurham regularly to court Teresa and Martha Blount, sisters from the Catholic family who owned the house.",
