    whyCurious: "Swift Ditch contains the remains of what may be the oldest flash lock structure on the Thames, possibly dating from the twelfth century. Flash locks — a simple movable weir panel — were the predecessor of the pound lock and preceded all the familiar locks on the river today. This one was made redundant in 1790 and left to decay in peace.",
