    whyCurious: "Snipe and curlew breed in the wet grassland here — species that have disappeared from most of lowland England but persist at Pinkhill because traditional management has been maintained. In winter the ditches fill with water voles and the reedy edges hold water rails. It is one of those reserves where the wildlife seems to be operating without reference to the twenty-first century.",
