    whyCurious: "The village of Nuneham Courtenay was demolished in 1760 to clear the view from the new house and is one of the most cited examples of Georgian landlordism at its most extreme. Oliver Goldsmith's poem The Deserted Village is widely believed to have been inspired by Nuneham's fate. The landscape that replaced the village is beautiful; the ethical question remains.",
