    whyCurious: "Most people visit Avebury or Stonehenge without understanding the much larger sacred landscape around them. Walking north from Avebury on the Ridgeway, you enter Oxfordshire through a corridor of sarsen stones, barrow cemeteries and hillfort earthworks — a continuous sacred monument 20 miles long.",
