    whyCurious: "All mute swans on the Thames belong to the Crown, the Vintners or the Dyers — a 12th-century legal fiction still enforced by the Swan Marker. The upping passes through Oxfordshire in the third day. The skiffs fly the Royal Standard. The ceremony involves catching and examining swans and sounds completely implausible until you see it.",
