    whyCurious: "The toy collection was assembled from private donations over 30 years and contains pieces of genuine rarity — 1900s Steiff bears, original Meccano sets, pre-war tinplate. The town's Puritan history (the original Banbury Cross was destroyed by Puritans for being idolatrous) adds context to a place that also gave the world a children's nursery rhyme.",
