    whyCurious: "Lesser spotted woodpecker is now genuinely rare — a significant population decline has left it confined to a few traditional woodlands. Bernwood is one of the most reliable sites in England. The combination of three woodpecker species plus hawfinches, marsh tit and bullfinch makes this a remarkable woodland bird site.",
