    whyCurious: "Most Eleanor Cross fragments disappeared at the Reformation. This fragment is in a churchyard and almost nobody knows its significance. The Eleanor Crosses are one of the great acts of medieval royal grief — Edward had 12 crosses built at every stopping point. The few surviving examples are among the best medieval sculpture in England.",
