    whyCurious: "Henley escaped Victorian development because it was prosperous enough not to need to rebuild its 18th-century buildings. The high street is an intact 1750-1830 townscape. The town trail picks up details invisible at walking pace: date stones, merchants' symbols and the varied brick bonds of an era without standardisation.",
