    whyCurious: "Wallingford was where the Empress Matilda held out against King Stephen for years, and where Henry II came to consolidate his kingship. The earthworks are larger than many English castles still standing in stone. The flint walls of the great tower are still 3 metres high. It's in a public park with deckchairs.",
