    description: "A public footpath following the Letcombe Brook from Wantage through the chalk spring-line villages of Letcombe Bassett and Letcombe Regis — a clear chalk stream with brown trout, water crowfoot in summer and the remains of Victorian watercress beds.",
    whyCurious: "Chalk streams are one of the rarest habitats in the world — 85% of the global total are in England. The Letcombe Brook is a textbook example: crystal clear, constant temperature, gravel bed, lined with water cress and brook lime. The footpath follows it closely enough that you're walking through it rather than beside it.",
