    description: "An artist near Thame runs workshops in encaustic painting — using molten beeswax mixed with damar resin and pigment, painted hot onto board, fused with heat guns and carved or layered to create translucent, luminous works in the same medium used by ancient Egyptian craftsmen.",
    whyCurious: "Encaustic is one of the oldest painting media — Roman Fayum portrait mummies were painted in encaustic. The technique produces colours of extraordinary depth and translucency. The physical process — working quickly with hot wax before it solidifies — forces a spontaneity that oil or watercolour don't require.",
