    description: "The surviving buildings of Abingdon Abbey — once one of the wealthiest in England — include three gatehouse structures and the Long Gallery, scattered through the town centre and riverside, freely accessible and largely uninterpreted.",
    whyCurious: "Abingdon Abbey was dissolved in 1538 and its buildings largely demolished. What remains is embedded in the modern town — a medieval gateway in a car park, a 15th-century checker building beside the river, a latrine block converted to a museum. Piecing together the layout from the fragments is a genuine puzzle.",
